wiki.content: “Wonder Woman” describes a strong and resilient woman who has lived a thousand lives and experienced pain, but still remains strong. The lyrics convey the message that sometimes even the strongest person can break down, and they may want to hide their vulnerability from others. However, the woman in the song wants to be perceived as someone who will never give up, even though she may cry behind closed doors. The slow piano production used in the song creates a melancholic atmosphere that can tug at the heartstrings of the listeners, perfectly matching the introspective and sorrowful lyrics. Miley’s emotive vocals blend seamlessly with the gentle yet haunting notes of the piano, enhancing the somber ambiance of the track. The slow tempo of the song allows for a deep dive into the emotions of the lyrics, and Miley’s voice effectively conveys the pain and vulnerability, making the listeners feel connected to the persona’s experiences. “Wonder Woman” can be highly reminiscent of some of Miley’s notable tracks like, “Slide Away,” “The Climb,” “Wrecking Ball,” “Adore You,” and “Malibu,” which have a similar theme about perseverance and personal growth, which are also present in the song.
